oncology

Entry Element BreastCancerTNMStage

Documentation:
The stage of a cancer, assessed according to the standard established by American Joint Committee on Cancer (AJCC). TNM Stage Grouping categorizes the progression of cancer using a modified Roman Numeral system.

      http://hl7.org/fhir/us/breastcancer/oncology/vs/BreastCancerStageVS (REQUIRED)
      StageTimingPrefix
      Indicates when the staging was done, in terms of treatment landmarks, either clinical (at diagnosis prior to treatment) (c), pathologic (post-surgical) (p), post-neoadjuvant clinical (yc), or post-neoadjuvant pathologic(yp). The stage timing code is prefix on the N stage. For example, for post-neoadjuvant clinical staging, the N categories are preceded by 'yc' (e.g. ycNX)
